This new k table is made to reduce the total number of subbands over the solar spectrum.
The total number of ks with this new tables is 148, which is significantly smaller than the original tables.
The reason for the reduction is new treatment of overlapping bands.
Instead of applying the multiplicative rule, water vapor is set to the major sonstituedts and the oter gase is set to minor constituent.
The concentration of minor gases are fixed to the mean mixing ration in the following table.



Band No.      Major      Minor      Number of subbands
16            H2O        O2            6
25            H2O        CO2           6
27            H2O        CO2           6
29            H2O        CO2           9
30            H2O        O3            7
31            H2O        CO2           7
32            H2O        CO2          15

The format of the table is exactly the same as before so that you can simply change old tables by new tables.

The new tables give slightly less absorption compared with old table as shown by the attached table.

These tables are based on HITRAN 96 except for band 16, which used HITRAN 2000.
(New tables using HITRAN 2000 for all bands will be available soon.)




